                                through puddles, kite bosses onto them, and overlap multiple puddles for guaranteed procs.
                                Never Pulverize an enemy not standing in poison.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong>Debilitating Roar for danger moments</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
                                When surrounded by dangerous elites or taking heavy damage, pop Debilitating Roar.
                                It reduces enemy damage output and generates a large chunk of Fortify via Preserving upgrade.
                                Also useful before boss burst windows for safety.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong>Trample to reposition + Unstoppable</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
                                Use Trample to break crowd control, gap close to new packs, or reposition onto fresh
                                puddles. Savage Trample also deals bonus damage based on remaining Fortify, so it's not
                                just utility &mdash; it hits hard when you are fully Fortified.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong>Calm Before the Storm resets Grizzly Rage</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
                                Your Wolf Spirit Boon (Calm Before the Storm) reduces Ultimate cooldown via Lucky Hit.
                                With Pulverize hitting many enemies per slam, you generate Lucky Hit procs rapidly,
                                often resetting Grizzly Rage before it even ends. Aim for near 100% uptime.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Boss Strategy</h2>
                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Single Target Bosses</strong>
                    <p>The rotation stays the same but puddle management becomes even more critical.
                    Attack the boss to lay down puddles, then position yourself to slam Pulverize while the boss stands in them.
                    Overpowers on a single target with full Willpower stacking will one-shot most boss health gates.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Uber Bosses / Pit Bosses</strong>
                    <p>Pre-cast Debilitating Roar for survivability. Open with Grizzly Rage, lay puddles with Claw,
                    then chain Pulverize. Save Trample as an emergency escape. The guaranteed Overpower damage scales
                    with your Maximum Life and Fortify &mdash; stack both as high as possible for Pit pushing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

